Metallon Corp CEO Gura Resigned, Company Said

-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a   a n d   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-07-08T14:53:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/metallon-corp-ceo-gura-resigned-company-said-1-.html
Collen Gura, chief executive officer
and chairman of Metallon Corp’s  Zimbabwe  unit, will leave the
company this month to pursue personal interests, the company
said .  Gura will be replaced by Allan Mashingaidze at the end of
the month, Metallon’s board said in an e-mailed statement today.  Metallon is Zimbabwe’s biggest gold miner by output, with
five mines. It is contolled by  South Africa ’s Mzi Khumalo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
